{"title":"Summarizing the auxiliary verbs","body":[{"type":"p","text":"In general, the independent verb follows after the auxiliary verb(s)."},{"type":"p","text":"We can distinguish four main types of auxiliary verb constructions:"},{"type":"table","table":[["hebben","to have","zijn","to be"],["worden","to become","raken","to get"]]},{"type":"p","text":"When the past participle itself serves as an auxiliary verb, the past participle turns into an infinitive."},{"type":"table","table":[["beweren","to claim","blijken","to appear"],["denken","to think","hopen","to hope"],["lijken","to seem","menen","to mean"],["schijnen","to seem","wensen","to wish"],["hebben","to have","hoeven","to need"],["komen","to come (to)","--","--"]]},{"type":"table","table":[["aanmoedigen","to encourage","streven","to strive"],["bedoelen","to intend, mean","verlangen","to long for"],["beloven","to promise","verzoeken","to request"],["bevelen","to command","vragen om","to ask for"],["opdragen","to command","wensen","to wish"],["proberen","to try","--","--"]]},{"type":"table","table":[["zitten","to sit","liggen","to lie"],["lopen","to walk","staan","to stand"],["hangen","to hang","--","--"]]},{"type":"table","table":[["blijven te","to remain -able","zijn te","to be -able"],["vallen","to be -able","--","--"]]},{"type":"table","table":[["durven","to dare","hoeven","to have to"],["hebben te","to have to","komen","to 'will happen'"]]},{"type":"table","table":[["blijven","to stay, keep","gaan","to go"],["komen","to come","kunnen","to be able"],["moeten","to have to","mogen","to be allowed"],["willen","to want","zullen","'to' will"]]},{"type":"table","table":[["horen","to hear","vinden","to find"],["voelen","to feel","zien","to see"]]},{"type":"p","text":"This construction is exclusively reserved for the 'aan het' continuous."},{"type":"p","text":"The auxiliary verb is always zijn (to be)."}]}